OL,3,CFirst section of refurbished Tyne
OL,4,CBridge revealed
OL,6,FTo date, the work has not always been
OL,7,Fobvious from the road, as it has been
OL,8,Ftaking place in a narrow gap in the
OL,9,Fstructure below the road.
OL,11,FThis has included removing nine tonnes
OL,12,Fof bird poo, the equivalent of three
OL,13,FLand Rover Defenders, so that the
OL,14,Fsteelwork could be repaired before
OL,15,Fbeing repainted.
OL,17,FIt is thought that throughout the
OL,18,Frestoration 139,400 litres of paint
OL,19,Fwill be used - enough to fill 850 beer
OL,20,Fbarrels.
OL,1,W~k4~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}        G4/7
